And that's okay, I mean for every person who decides they don't like a character there's another saying they loved that character and want to find more information on them. Go to those people. Give them recommendations. No point arguing with people who made up their mind.

The point is different interpretations come with different mediums, and with different interpretations comes new people who will see that story and they'll judge Superman, or any comic character, by that story. They're not going to read a comic because they've already decided.

But that's how it goes. Why do you think we as Superman fans criticize how he's written in other mediums. ‚ÄúHe's not bright enough‚Äù ‚ÄúHe shouldn't kill‚Äù ‚ÄúHe's not giving hopeful vibes‚Äù because our first impression were these things. Especially in comics. This is how we see Superman

They'll say well he's too strong to be interesting, because all they care about his how hard a character can punch. Well he's a boy scout, because there's something wrong with being good for people these days. Do I agree with the reasoning people come up with? No. Tbh it's dumb.
